{
  "texts": [
    "GMM parameters are calculated using differentiable computing module and the optimal transformation is recovered.",
    "Different from the way of voxelizing point cloud, Ali et al. (2021) proposed RPSRNet, which used the tree representation based on Barnes Hut (BH) (Barnes and Hut, 1986) for the input point cloud data.",
    "First, the model recursively subdivides the normalized boundary space of the input point cloud to the limit depth to construct the BH tree.",
    "With the help of the established index of the tree and the hash graph (Bader, 2012), the network can retrieve the neighborhood portion of a given node.",
    "Secondly, the layered feature extraction (HFE) module is embedded in the model for global feature extraction."
  ]
}